      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Pray convey also my best felicitations to him and his future lady, ¶  ¶ at this happy and auspicious event. To me it is particularly significant, because Mr. Barnard is a scion of the family ¶  ¶ o...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.08.00e</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Charles French</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from the obituary notice of Francis G. A. Barnard,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victorian naturalist</seg>, vol.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>49<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1932), p. 72. The quoted text is introduced by 'in a letter to Mr. C. French, senr, the secretary<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[i.e.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Charles French Snr; standard disambiguation note added for ease of retrieval in searches],<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Baron von Mueller writes:'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Francis<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>George<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Allman<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Barnard<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was married to Mary Rachel Watts<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 20 August 1889 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 31 August<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1889, p. 1), and the letter is dated accordingly.<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray convey also my best felicitations to him and his future lady,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at this happy and auspicious event. To me it is particularly significant, because Mr. Barnard is a scion of the family<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on which Sir Edwin<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Smith,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sir<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>James Edward<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Smith,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>referred to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>directly<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the author of the obituary, who<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>wrote<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that Barnard<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'through his mother<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>… was a descendant of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sir James Edwin Smith, founder of the Linnean Society of London'.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who just 100 years ago founded the Linnean Society, shed such lustre. ...<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ellipsis in source text.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The bridegroom whom we wish to honour on this great<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>occasion<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has evidently inherited the Smithian spirit, of which, by his zealous services to the Club,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Field Naturalists'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Club of Victoria.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he has given such ample proof.</p>
         </div>
